          "body": "Verses 3-5 unpack the consequences of the dawning light through three vivid images. First, *the gladness of harvest* — the year's full barns, the year's full bellies, the year's deepest agricultural relief — pictures the kingdom's joy. Second, *the dividing of spoil* — the elated chaos after a battlefield victory — pictures the same joy from the warrior's angle. Third and most precisely, the deliverance comes *as at the battle of Midian* (9:4), Gideon's 300 against the host of 135,000 (Judges 7) — a deliverance accomplished without human strength, through divine intervention. Verse 5's image is unforgettable: the warrior's blood-soaked boot and cloak become *fuel for the fire*. War's instruments become firewood when the Prince of Peace reigns."
